1920 Izhevsk Hex Model 91 Dragoon. Extra notch stripper clip guide, low wall, machined rear, inner reciever step.

postcontent:
These are rare, I get them approximately twice a year, and hey sell off almost instantly.

The rifle has a threaded barrel, a picatinny rail, and an oversized bolt handle. Please see my review here: http://www.preciseshooter.com/blog/SavageMKIIFVSR.aspx

This is a DEALER transaction - NICS check is required, and taxes are additional.

FAQ - PLEASE READ! I am not going to respond to questions that are covered here!

Q. I am interested in your gun. Is it still available?
A. If you see this ad, most likely. The firearms are reserved for pickup on my web site, by making an appointment to buy. Someone could be doing it right now, and first person to reserve the firearm wins. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment on the site. If someone has made it just before you, I will notify you within a short time (usually, an hour), otherwise - see you shortly.

PLEASE DO NOT ASK WHETHER THE GUN IS STILL AVAILABLE! I WILL NOT RESPOND.

Q. How do I buy?
A. This is a dealer listing, NICS check, taxes, etc are all required. Please go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick up.

Q. I am interested in your gun. Call me @ xxx-xxx-xxxx
A. Excellent. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick it up.

Q. Are there any other fees, in addition to the price and taxes? NICS, background check, etc?
A. No.

Q. What is the tax rate?
A. 9.5%

Q. Where are you located?
A. Queen Anne neighborhood in Seattle.

Q. Can we meet in Burien on Monday morning?
A. No, FFL requirements are that the transfers happen at a licensed location. Also, the only times you can come over are the appointments that you can reserve on the site. No other time slots are available.

Q. I see you carry Savage rifles. Can you find me MKII FV-SR?
A. No. Please see here for what I can or cannot do: http://www.preciseshooter.com/NotInStock.aspx

Q. Do you take trades?
A. Sometimes. However:
a) firearms only,
b) they need to be our of current production (I can get new ones at wholesale prices), or you have to offer them to me at well below wholesale
c) I do not resell the trades, so they should fit my personal interests (which only include military as well as highly accurate, competition guns - no self defense guns like Glocks, M&Ps, XD*, and the like)
d) the exchange rate should be fair (see here for more: http://www.preciseshooter.com/blog/PriceGuide.aspx

Q. Is the price firm? Will you take XXX (70% of the asking price)?
A. The price is firm.

Q. Can you help me mount a scope/replace a trigger/fix a feeding problem?
A. Sorry, I do not do gunsmithing.

Q. Will you ship?
A. Yes - go to www.preciseshooter.com -> How to buy and read the section for buying outside Seattle area. Shipping on this rifle would be $25

- Meprolight Night Sights -- 3-dot
- Vickers extended magazine release.
- Glock 17 smooth trigger

Pistol will come with four mags: 1x 10-round mag, 2x 15-round mags, 1x 17-round mag.  All mags are Glock OEM.

It MUST be legal for you to own this firearm.  I'll need to see a Tennessee photo ID upon sale/trade.

----------TRADES----------

With the ammo, I'll take down the price according to what you give me.  If it's a firearm, we'll work out a fair trade.  May add cash for the right deal.  If you are offering a firearm for trade, please go ahead and e-mail me a picture when you contact me.  

Firearms:
- .22LR or .22MAG pistol (prefer with a bit of ammo).  Revolver or semi-auto is fine, but would really like a single-action revolver.
- .357MAG lever action rifle.  Looking for a Rossi or a used Marlin or Winchester.  
- 12GA shotgun -- Remington, Mossberg, or Benelli Nova -- with 18" or 20" barrel.  Prefer extended mag tube.  
- Anything else you think might interest me.  If it's not on this list, know that I'm not really interested in anything worth over $550.  I am not interested in hunting rifles, hunting shotguns, or .22LR rifles.  I may look at a .45 pistol, but I don't need anymore .40s, 9mms, or .38s.  

Ammo:
- .22LR ammo.  Only looking for a brick or two -- need to teach a new shooter.  As a nod to the (ridiculous) times we live in, I'll value a 500-round box at $50 and a 325-round box at $35.  If they're 50-round boxes, I'll give $5 each.  
- 9mm hollowpoint ammo -- must be 124gr or heavier (unless it's Cor-Bon), cannot be Winchester White Box (100rd value pack) or Federal Hydrashok.  Brands: Winchester Ranger, Winchester PDX, Federal HST, Remington Golden Saber, Speer Gold Dot, Cor-Bon DPX (will be 115gr).  If it's not from one of the listed brands, I am not interested.
- .40S&W hollowpoint ammo -- no Federal Hydrashok.  Prefer 180gr, but will take other weights.  Brands: Winchester Ranger, Winchester PDX, Federal HST, Remington Golden Saber, Speer Gold Dot, Cor-Bon DPX.  If it's not from one of the listed brands, I am not interested.
- .38SPL hollowpoint ammo -- Must be either Cor-Bon DPX 110gr or Speer Gold Dot 135gr +P.  If it's not from one of the listed brands, I am not interested.
- 5.56/.223 ammo -- Must be 5.56 pressure if FMJ.  If .223, must be a soft point or hollow point.  No steel case.
